comment._content:
This aircraft is ID as follows
Me-262A-1a Swallow  JF(2)  Ger WWII
with (fn) Fuselage Number Black KD+EA is very identifiable,
but, the (wn) worke nummer is only faintly to be seen & NOT recognizable.
Comments
Me-262x-xx AC (Aircraft) of all types,of which there were over (1) variables
do not give indication of the Weapons systems by their Type call out A-1a or standard Jet Fighter.  White the standard was, as with this AC, which is visually apparent, to have
(4) M-108 30mm Nose Cannon's. (two on this side are visble)  
The device to the left of the nose wheel is a Quick Shot or Battery Charger - power source
used on the flight line.
